title: PCM’s Ellens, Mustang girls finish third at Saydel
text:
PCM’s Ellens, Mustang girls finish third at Saydel Published: Friday, Oct. 16, 2015 10:45 a.m. CDT By Troy Hyde Newton Daily News 
DES MOINES — Prairie City-Monroe’s cross country teams got one last tune up before next week’s state qualifying meet at Columbus Community. 
The Mustangs competed in the Saydel Eagles Cross Country Invitational and junior Chris Ellens came home with a third-place individual finish in the boys’ 5K, while the Mustang girls also finished third as a team. 
Ellens put together a nice performance and nearly snagged the runner-up spot as his time of 17 minutes, 52.81 seconds was .64 seconds behind Saydel’s Nathen Nelson. 
North Polk’s Austin Smith won the race in 17:35. 
The Comets cruised to the team title with 33 points, while Ballard was second with 87 points. 
Nevada (111), Carlisle (132) and Perry (163) rounded out the top five, while PCM finished in ninth of the 10-team field with 179 points. 
Mustang sophomore Blake Lee was the second PCM runner to finish. 
Lee hit the line in 19th place with a time of 18:56.35, while sophomore Brady North was 63rd, sophomore Noah Henkenius ended up 68th and senior Andres Vargas was the fifth and final counting place in 86th. 
Senior Max Van Gorp (99th), junior Braden Phifer (102nd), sophomore Caleb Peter (104th), sophomore Bradley McClellan (110th) and Jonathan Heath (136th) also competed for the Mustangs. 
Like the boys race, North Polk, ranked No. 7 in Class 2A, won the girls team title with ease. 
The Comets had the first three finishers and six in the top 12 and scored 25 points. 
Ballard (46) was the runner-up, while PCM finished third with 118 points. 
The rest of the top five of the eight-team field included Nevada (123) and Greene County (132). Pella Christian (167), Saydel (169) and Perry (170) finalized the field. 
Junior Jayci Vos and freshman Payton Schut led the way for the Mustangs in 16th and 17th place, respectively. Vos crossed the line in 22:27.04, while Schut was .36 seconds behind. 
Sophomore Baylee Smith ended up in 27th with a time of 23:33.21, while freshman Morgan Uhlenhopp, freshman Sara Dudley and senior Morgan Novak came across the line in 39th, 40th and 41st, respectively. 
Junior Mallery Downey (67th) and senior Mallory Bell (79th) also ran for the Mustangs. 
PCM’s Class 2A state qualifier is at 4 p.m. Thursday at Columbus Community in Columbus Junction.
